com.ibm.avatar.api.tam

Interface ModuleMetadata


  • public interface ModuleMetadata
    This class provides APIs to retrieve metadata of various AQL elements from the loaded ModuleMetadata object. An instance of this type can be obtained by invoking one of the APIs in ModuleMetadataFactory class. There are APIs to fetch the list of AQL elements, which are either marked as exported through a variant of export statement, and/or as external through a variant of create external statement; all the AQL element names returned by these APIs are qualified by containing module name except for the one which belongs to 'genericModule'.
    Note: Non-modular AQLs are compiled into a special module called 'genericModule'. There are additional APIs per AQL element type to fetch detailed metadata based on the element name.

    There is an additional API to fetch module names on which this module depends on.

    See Also:
    CompileAQL

        List<Pair<String,String>> getExternalViews()
        Returns list of external view name pairs, where the first element of the pair is the view name as declared in an AQL create external view statement. For modular AQL, the view name returned will be qualified with containing module name; the second argument is the external name as declared in an AQL create external view statement's external_name clause.
        Returns:
        list of external view name pairs

      • getOutputViews

        String[] getOutputViews()
        Returns a list of names of the views marked as output view through the output view statement. Names returned are either output view aliases created through output view statement's 'as' clause, a view name qualified by containing module name if alias is not declared, or an unqualified view name for genericModule (module compiled from non-modular AQLs).
        Returns:
        an array of output view names

      • getViewMetadata

        ViewMetadata getViewMetadata(String viewName)
        Returns view metadata of a given view name.
        Parameters:
        viewName - this name can be one of the following: an output alias, an external name (in case of external view), the fully qualified name for modular AQLs, an unqualified view name inside a genericModule(module generate for non-modular AQL code), or the view Document
        Returns:
        view metadata object; null, if metadata not found for the given view name
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if multiple matches are found in the metadata for the given view name

      • getComment

        String getComment()
        Returns the text of the AQL doc comment associated with this module. The text of the original comment read from the file "module.info" in the source module directory is processed as follows:
        • Leading comment separator (/**) and trailing comment separator (*/) are removed
        • Leading asterisk (*) characters on each line are discarded; blanks and tabs preceding the initial asterisk (*) characters are also discarded. If you omit the leading asterisk on a line, the leading white space is not removed.
        • Carriage return characters (\r) are removed.
        Returns:
        the text of the AQL doc comment with leading (begin AQL doc comment) and trailing (end AQL doc comment) separators discarded, leading consecutive whitespace followed by an asterisk on each line of the comment also discarded, carriage return characters (\r) also discarded

      • getComment

        String getComment(ModuleMetadata.ElementType type,
                  String name)
           throws InvalidModuleElementException
        Retrieve the text of the AQL doc comment associated with the given element of the given type.
        Parameters:
        type - type of element
        name - qualified name of the element. For elements of type ModuleMetadata.ElementType.VIEW,this name be either be an output alias, fully qualified name,external name (in case of external view), or unqualified name for view inside a genericModule(module generated for non-modular AQL)
        Returns:
        string contains the AQL doc comment associated for given element name
        Throws:
        InvalidModuleElementException - if an element of the given type with the given name does not exist

      • getDependsOn

        @Deprecated
String getDependsOn()
        Deprecated. As of v2.1, replaced by getDependentModules()
        Returns the list of module names that the current module depends on. Module A is considered to depend on module B if it directly imports module B, or an artifact of module B. Indirect (transitive) dependencies are not returned. Example: Module A imports module B, which in turn imports module C. By this definition, A depends on B, and does not depend on C.
        Returns:
        comma-separated list of dependent module names

      • getDependentModules

        List<String> getDependentModules()
        Returns a list of module names that the current module depends on. Module A is considered to depend on module B if it directly imports module B, or an artifact of module B. Indirect (transitive) dependencies are not returned. Example: Module A imports module B, which in turn imports module C. By this definition, A depends on B, and does not depend on C.
        Returns:
        List of module names that the current module depends on
